On to finishing Lucille number two (a commission) in White Oak, my least favorite wood to work.
Everything nice about Walnut is awful with White Oak.  Not easily shaped with a rasp and scraper due to the differentiation in hardness in early wood and late wood which means I need to whip out all of the slicing tools I have.
This crazy old Millers Falls spokeshave, given to me by @joshvillegas94 when he decided to go full kanna, is the perfect tool for these inside curves. 
Nicely honed and with a steady hand, I should be finishing this one in a day or two.

Via @ronanerwanbouroullec, a plywood backrest and plywood seat held together by a central wooden bridge.

Quindici, 2017
"Quindici is after Osso in 2011 and Uncino in 2014 our third collection developed together with Mattiazzi.
While the first two collaborations explored the rather computerized manufacturing possibilities of Mattiazzi, Quindici is constructed in a more direct and traditional manner. The plywood backrest and plywood seat are held together by a central wooden bridge. The sides and armrests are build up of wooden planks.
Due to its construction there is a strong emphasis on the silhouette which was designed to meet ergonomic demands - the reclined seating position, the headrest and its generous armrests invite to read, to reflect, to relax, to nap...
An upholstered version not only adds physical comfort but also colour - all pieces exist in natural, black or grey ash wood.
Quindici comes as a Chaise Longue as well as a lounge chair." #design #chair #chaiselongue #loungechair #mattiazzisrl #bouroullec
